!!!Other conventions 

Note that also file names used by us inlcude some metadata already. For instance:
*sms19610000lagercrantz318
*sjd20150609aaa-sport
where the first three letters __sms_ or _sjd_ - in accordance with ISO 639-3 - always mark the language (or main language) of a given session 1961 and the following eight digits always mark the data of a given session in the format YYYYMMDD. If the exact date is unknown or cannot be specified (e.g. in a book publication were only the year is given) we use the digit 0.


